00:43:55.550 --> 00:43:57.250
virtual world.

00:43:57.250 --> 00:44:01.670
Do you get any sense that over time humans
will become more sophisticated about what's

00:44:01.670 --> 00:44:06.400
happening in this world and what's being done
and will that make a difference to their reactions

00:44:06.400 --> 00:44:07.910
in this space?

00:44:07.910 --> 00:44:10.710
Because we seem to get more sophisticated
about other technology.

00:44:10.710 --> 00:44:12.920
&gt;&gt;Jeremy: It's a great question.

00:44:12.920 --> 00:44:17.170
So the question is subjects in my studies
may not have known anything about VR and as

00:44:17.170 --> 00:44:21.640
we get used to the technology, none of this
is going to work.

00:44:21.640 --> 00:44:25.570
I think there's a good truth to that which
is there is a novelty effect what we're going

00:44:25.570 --> 00:44:29.369
to see is an arms race very similar to spam
and spam blockers.

00:44:29.369 --> 00:44:34.670
People using these transformations, people
realizing they're not real, and then someone

00:44:34.670 --> 00:44:37.210
having to go to the next level and going back
and forth.

00:44:37.210 --> 00:44:41.250
One thing I like to say is my purpose is to
