00:44:41.250 --> 00:44:44.490
With the political morphing, I get approached
by political consultants sometimes.

00:44:44.490 --> 00:44:46.079
I just don't do that work.

00:44:46.079 --> 00:44:48.700
I view my goal as informing the public.

00:44:48.700 --> 00:44:52.640
And when you consciously are aware of this
stuff, so when I tell you that candidate has

00:44:52.640 --> 00:44:54.790
stolen your face, that backfires.

00:44:54.790 --> 00:44:57.150
And so, this is truly a case of knowledge
is power.

00:44:57.150 --> 00:45:00.500
And then the question is how sophisticated
are the users compared to the people trying

00:45:00.500 --> 00:45:01.869
the transformations.

00:45:01.869 --> 00:45:08.290
&gt;&gt; Male #3: So, could you give us an idea
what things avatars don't work for?

00:45:08.290 --> 00:45:12.030
You must have had some negative results over
the years.

00:45:12.030 --> 00:45:15.530
&gt;&gt; Jeremy: So, great question.

00:45:15.530 --> 00:45:17.330
There's many things that don't work.

00:45:17.330 --> 00:45:21.000
Those, academia doesn't reward you for publishing
things that don't work.

00:45:21.000 --> 00:45:23.859
One thing we tried was whites and blacks.

00:45:23.859 --> 00:45:28.030
We took white people and put them in black
avatars and forced them to walk a day in the

00:45:28.030 --> 00:45:32.410
shoe of someone who's black with the idea
we wanted them to gain an empathy.

00:45:32.410 --> 00:45:35.030
And that was the case where we didn't actually
reduce racism.

00:45:35.030 --> 00:45:36.660
We actually increased it.

00:45:36.660 --> 00:45:41.121
So there's a fairly large literature on racial
priming which is that some whites, when you

00:45:41.121 --> 00:45:45.530
remind them of blacks, that changes their
behavior in a negative way just because it's

00:45:45.530 --> 00:45:46.900
called priming.

00:45:46.900 --> 00:45:50.869
Unfortunately American whites generally have
negative associations in general with blacks.

00:45:50.869 --> 00:45:55.280
We thought if we put you in an avatar and
show you what it's like to be a different

00:45:55.280 --> 00:45:59.020
race that would help and this is one instance
where it backfired on us and we're still doing

00:45:59.020 --> 00:46:00.869
follow ups on that.

00:46:00.869 --> 00:46:04.279
I can talk for hours about the studies that
haven't worked.

00:46:04.279 --> 00:46:11.830
&gt;&gt; Male #4: The studies that rely on mainly
